1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 2=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:39,920
What on earth is this?

4
00:00:52,590 --> 00:00:53,460
Chen,

5
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:55,560
I think something just hit our boat.

6
00:01:00,390 --> 00:01:02,110
Dad, there's something in the water.

7
00:01:02,750 --> 00:01:04,480
Something? What?

8
00:01:04,510 --> 00:01:05,350
What is it?

9
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,680
Chen, look!

10
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,840
Is that a fish?

11
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,040
How big must it be to do that?

12
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:34,880
Hold on tight!

13
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:43,790
I saw it!

14
00:01:43,790 --> 00:01:45,560
Over there! It's a fish!

15
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,346
It's swimming right at us!

16
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:53,560
It's coming!

17
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,510
You angered the River King!

18
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:56,400
You brought this to us!

19
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,400
Get down!

20
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,800
We're losing control of the boat!

21
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:17,960
- Drop the anchor.
- Sure.

22
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,030
We're doomed.

23
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:22,630
The boat's not moving at all.

24
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:25,360
Guess we're fish food now.

25
00:03:02,430 --> 00:03:05,630
Please calm down, River King.

26
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:16,280
Please calm down, River King.

27
00:03:18,910 --> 00:03:21,870
Please calm down, River King.

28
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:31,750
Chen,

29
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,660
do you think that giant fish

30
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,190
will come back?

31
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,150
Let's hope it doesn't.

32
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,520
This is fresh water.

33
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,800
How can a fish be that big?

34
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:44,400
Some of these freshwater fish

35
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,960
have been around for ages.

36
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,800
If their habitat

37
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,080
stayed untouched,

38
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,190
it's not strange that they grew huge.

39
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:53,430
But still,

40
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,240
a fish that massive?

41
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:57,590
Guess no one's eating sashimi
from that fish.

42
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,840
We'll just brew its head.

43
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,000
Even if you want to brew it,

44
00:04:01,011 --> 00:04:02,560
where are you gonna find a pot that big?

45
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:03,430
Right now,

46
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:05,360
let's wait till they fix the boat.

47
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:10,560
Chubby! Chubby!

48
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,400
Chubby!

49
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:12,550
Chen!

50
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:13,800
Chubby!

51
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,960
The military shovel!

52
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,950
The shovel's right here!

53
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:20,760
The shovel!

54
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:26,680
- Chen!
- The shovel!

55
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:27,830
Hold on tight!

56
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:31,510
Chen, harder! Come on!

57
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,390
Harder, Chen!

58
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,560
Chen, chop it!

59
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,400
Chop it!

60
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,190
Dad, these people are tomb raiders.

61
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,310
Commander Chen, thanks.

62
00:04:47,950 --> 00:04:48,800
You too.

63
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,120
This fish keeps following us.

64
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,600
Maybe it smells something?

65
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,270
How about we toss the sack overboard?

66
00:04:58,270 --> 00:05:00,070
Feed it, and maybe it'll leave.

67
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:04,560
What are you doing?

68
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:06,630
The River King is angry

69
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:07,950
because of you.

70
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:10,720
Hey, don't talk like that.

71
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,750
We don't even know that thing.

72
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:14,160
You think I don't know?

73
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,630
I heard what you said;

74
00:05:16,870 --> 00:05:18,190
I saw what's in your bags.

75
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,310
They prove you're tomb raiders.

76
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,560
The earthy smell on you

77
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,040
angered the River King.

78
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,240
- Hey, chill.
- Bro!

79
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,950
First of all, we're not tomb raiders.

80
00:05:26,950 --> 00:05:27,790
Shut up.

81
00:05:29,390 --> 00:05:31,430
I've been sailing here
for over ten years.

82
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,950
I've never seen anything like this.

83
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,160
Surely,

84
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,560
it's because of you.

85
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,750
Get off this boat now.

86
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,430
Wait, wait, bro.

87
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,120
It's all water out there.

88
00:05:40,270 --> 00:05:41,720
Where do you want us to go?

89
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,040
Will you jump yourselves?

90
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,950
Or should I give you a little push?

91
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,310
Dude, put it down first.

92
00:05:46,310 --> 00:05:47,390
- Put it down.
- Bro.

93
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:48,950
- No.
- Wait!

94
00:05:49,070 --> 00:05:49,910
Bro!

95
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:52,200
- Bro!
- Put that down!

96
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:55,350
Lu!

97
00:05:58,870 --> 00:05:59,870
- Lu!
- Lu!

98
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,360
- Lu!
- Grab a rope!

99
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:02,600
Find a pole and pull him up!

100
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:17,390
- Lu, grab this!
- It's coming!

101
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:18,560
Grab this!

102
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,800
Lu! Lu!

103
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,120
Grab it!

104
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,600
The fish is coming!

105
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,190
Hurry, Lu!

106
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:26,680
Grab it, Lu!

107
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,800
Chen, think of something!

108
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,800
Look!

109
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:32,830
Don't move around.

110
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:34,190
Lu, grab it now!

111
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,200
Any weapons?

112
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,600
Any fuel?

113
00:06:38,610 --> 00:06:39,423
Yeah.

114
00:06:39,434 --> 00:06:40,425
- We have fuel!
- Fuel!

115
00:06:40,436 --> 00:06:41,560
Hurry!

116
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,400
Hurry up!

117
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:41,020
(Inn)

118
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:41,880
Let's stop here.

119
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,070
Nowhere else ahead.

120
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:44,910
Let's stop here.

121
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:47,160
Hello, sir.

122
00:07:47,310 --> 00:07:48,150
Sir.

123
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:49,560
Do you have any rooms?

124
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,040
How many do you need?

125
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:53,680
Just one.

126
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:55,910
Sure.

127
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:09,030
Sir,

128
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,310
what kind of fish are you offering?

129
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,870
That's not a fish.

130
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,920
I'm praying

131
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:17,160
to the Azure River King.

132
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:18,960
The river god?

133
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:20,110
Exactly.

134
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,950
So, we actually met

135
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:23,360
the river god.

136
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,070
You saw the river god?

137
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,270
Yeah, right there in the river.

138
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:31,630
Dark head, azure scales?

139
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,080
That size

140
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:36,440
is as big as several trucks?

141
00:08:36,790 --> 00:08:37,720
Anyway, it's pretty big.

142
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:39,750
Sir,

143
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,600
when was the last time

144
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:43,510
the Azure River King showed up?

145
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:47,150
That was back when I was young.

146
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:49,080
There was an outsider.

147
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,550
Somehow, he insisted

148
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,870
on catching the River King
to offer up to the heavens.

149
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:55,910
At that time,

150
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:57,960
there was a pair in the river,

151
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,360
one male, one female.

152
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,630
He went for the female one.

153
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,670
After he caught it,

154
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:07,120
he ended up crippling one of his legs.

155
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:09,630
The female River King's body

156
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,630
was left on the riverbank,

157
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,373
right in the peak of midsummer,

158
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:14,840
when it was hottest.

159
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,670
It started rotting within two days.

160
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,720
The county got worried about diseases.

161
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:22,750
They sliced off the meat
and burned it all.

162
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,870
Only the bones were left.

163
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,150
It was pretty big.

164
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:28,960
Maybe out of guilt

165
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:31,150
or fear of punishment,

166
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:32,790
they offered money

167
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:35,120
to build a temple for the fish bones.

168
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,840
A temple for the fish bones?

169
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:39,510
That's right.

170
00:09:40,630 --> 00:09:42,790
The temple was in Yunling.

171
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,840
Back then,

172
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,630
many frequented there.

173
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:48,910
Then people said it was haunted.

174
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:51,750
A visitor once got scared
out of their mind there.

175
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:54,790
After that, no one dared to go anymore.

176
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,440
We've been wandering here for hours

177
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,630
and haven't even seen a public toilet.

178
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,030
Don't you think

179
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:16,030
we might've been tricked?

180
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:16,870
No way.

181
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,150
I called Curator Zhu last night.

182
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:20,870
Our analysis was spot on.

183
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,120
The temple is on this mountain.

184
00:10:26,790 --> 00:10:27,910
There's someone living here.

185
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:30,630
Let's go ask them.

186
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:32,670
Chen, Chen!

187
00:10:35,790 --> 00:10:36,910
In the middle of nowhere,

188
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,720
suddenly, a small house appears.

189
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:41,030
Don't you think that's a bit strange?

190
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:43,080
You've watched
too much Journey to the West.

191
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:46,550
Why are you guys so unguarded?

192
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,870
Better safe than sorry.

193
00:10:49,270 --> 00:10:50,360
We're three grown men.

194
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,630
- What's there to fear?
- Yes.

195
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:52,470
Let's move.

196
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:54,850
It smells like they're cooking chicken.

197
00:10:55,150 --> 00:10:55,990
Let's check it out.

198
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,240
Anyone home?

199
00:11:13,030 --> 00:11:13,870
Hello there!

200
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:21,360
Lu, Chen, hurry up!

201
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:22,800
Look.

202
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:24,480
No one's around.

203
00:11:24,510 --> 00:11:26,550
Why eat this chicken first?

204
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:28,360
We can pay when someone shows up.

205
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,630
Just smell it.

206
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:31,360
It's a free-range chicken.

207
00:11:31,790 --> 00:11:32,960
Fed only with grain.

208
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:36,560
Who are you?

209
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:40,440
Sir, we got lost in the mountains.

210
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,240
- Yeah.
- We need some water.

211
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,080
Yeah, exactly.

212
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:44,440
Water's not the point.

213
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:47,000
Sir, do you sell this chicken?

214
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:49,840
I raised the chicken

215
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,720
since it was small.

216
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,720
City folks like you

217
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,510
would never taste anything like this.

218
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:01,870
Here.

219
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:05,550
This is amazing.

220
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:06,960
If you like it,

221
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:08,440
add some more.

222
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,440
Got it.

223
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,550
Are you guys here for sightseeing?

224
00:12:15,390 --> 00:12:16,600
Or doing geology work?

225
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:19,920
Sightseeing.

226
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,080
Yeah.

227
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:24,080
We might dig up some local goods too.

228
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:25,510
So it's not a wasted trip.

229
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,160
Around here,

230
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,840
it's pretty remote.

231
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,910
Not much fun to be had.

232
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:33,720
We heard there's a River King Temple.

233
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:36,270
We followed the map
and searched for ages,

234
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,550
but couldn't find it.

235
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,510
Do you know the way to get there?

236
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,270
That's normal

237
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:42,710
if you can't find it.

238
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:45,320
This is a secret place in Yunling.

239
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:47,120
The terrain's really tricky.

240
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:48,840
The tourist maps

241
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:50,320
only show a rough direction.

242
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:52,360
If you want the exact spot,

243
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:54,750
you can't just follow the map.

244
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:58,870
How did the chicken soup get me tipsy?

245
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,790
Lu, Chubby.

246
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:29,150
How dare you kill us

247
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,550
in broad daylight?

248
00:13:32,030 --> 00:13:33,390
Anyone who comes for the tomb

249
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,150
deserves death.

250
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:37,270
Who exactly are you?

251
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,000
Whether we're looking for a tomb

252
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:40,139
is none of your business.

253
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:41,630
You're the tomb keeper?

254
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,120
Alright, that's enough.

255
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,560
Listen to me.

256
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:50,443
It's not just the three of us this time.

257
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,840
We've got hundreds of colleagues.

258
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:53,910
They're in the county.

259
00:13:54,390 --> 00:13:56,360
They know we came here today.

260
00:13:56,550 --> 00:13:58,320
If we don't make it back before dark,

261
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,030
you'll pay the price.

262
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,960
Keep making things up.

263
00:14:02,230 --> 00:14:03,090
Old man,

264
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,270
don't doubt me.

265
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,600
Our team members

266
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:07,440
are well-equipped.

267
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:10,000
We got trucks loaded with gear.

268
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,910
If they can't find us,

269
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,440
forget this shabby house.

270
00:14:13,743 --> 00:14:15,080
They'd blow up the whole mountain.

271
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:15,920
Do you believe that?

272
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:22,800
See?

273
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,600
The full assault has begun.

274
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:35,840
He even has a gun.

275
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,340
That's a handmade flintlock.

276
00:14:37,510 --> 00:14:38,750
He probably made it himself.

277
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:40,560
He ran off.

278
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:43,320
Who is

279
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:44,510
cooperating with us?

280
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,870
This tomb is no ordinary one.

281
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,120
It even has a tomb keeper.

282
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,200
Miss Bai,

283
00:15:23,670 --> 00:15:24,600
it's still a fake tomb.

284
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:26,550
Miss Bai.

285
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:37,103
They've gone into the mountain.

286
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,790
But we lost their trail.

287
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,240
Useless.

288
00:15:42,390 --> 00:15:44,200
We got word from the innkeeper.

289
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,550
They left at 7 am...

290
00:15:48,630 --> 00:15:49,470
Stay alert.

291
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:50,750
Two o'clock direction.

292
